item.title: Building Computer
item.dc:creator: @West7man West7man
item.description:
@West7man wrote:

what about core i7 2600k? its cheap and powerful, supports more instructions. Maybe the mobo for sandy bridge cpus costs more… but hopefully you can survive that.
Intel Core i7-2600K 9,721 points
AMD Phenom II X6 1100T 6,287 points
(passmark benchmarks)
Ram looks okay.
I checked the prizes in EU, 2600K costs 250 euros, 2600 costs 225 euros and the phenom processor costs 170 euros.
I wouldnt go with the phenom cpu because they are aging. The sandy bridge i7 just came out and it is very cheap.
Better tell about your budget, how much can you give for a mobo + cpu?
